'''Lopo de Brito''' was the second [[List of Captains of Portuguese Ceylon|Captain]] of [[Portuguese Ceylon]]. Brito succeeded [[Jo<U+00E3>o da Silveira]] and was appointed in 1518 under [[Manuel I of Portugal]], he was Captain until 1522. He was succeeded by [[Fern<U+00E3>o Gomes de Lemos]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Captains|url=http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Sri_Lanka.html|work=Sri Lanka|publisher=World Statesmen.org|accessdate=17 February 2012}}</ref> 

